Refactor: Playoff bracket tree layout (Liquipedia style)

Backend (bracket_service.py):
- group_playoff_rounds() now returns {upper, lower, grand} dict with OrderedDict
  per section, rounds sorted by bracket sequence
- _match_short_label() helper for column headers (strips CK/NR prefix)
- bracket_service now exports _match_label, _match_short_label as Jinja2 globals

App (app.py):
- Register _match_label and _match_short_label as Jinja2 globals
  so they can be called directly from templates

Template (tournament.html):
- New Playoffs section structure:
  <div class="playoff-tree">
    <div class="upper-bracket">
      <div class="bracket-label">Nhanh Thang</div>
      <div class="bracket-rounds"> [columns] </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grand-final-column"> [vertical separator] </div>
    <div class="lower-bracket">
      <div class="bracket-label">Nhanh Thua</div>
      <div class="bracket-rounds"> [columns] </div>
    </div>
  </div>
- Each .bracket-column has fixed height (auto via flex), uses space-around to center matches
- Match boxes wrapped in .match-box-wrapper for connector positioning
- Position classes (first-in-column, last-in-column, middle-in-column) for vertical connector lines

New partial (templates/tournament/_match_box.html):
- Compact 2-row match card
- Grid layout: logo + name + score-box
- Map details hidden by default, shown on hover (.match-maps-detail)
- Edit button (pencil icon) only visible on hover
- Roll button (bottom-right) only visible on hover for pending matches
- Grand final match has special gold border + GRAND FINAL badge

CSS (static/style.css, ~250 lines):
- .playoff-tree: flex column with 50px gap between brackets
- .upper-bracket, .lower-bracket: flex row with fixed heights
  (upper: 560px, lower: 720px)
- .bracket-rounds: flex row with 40px gap between columns
- .bracket-column: flex column, justify-content: space-around
  - height: 100% to fill parent (auto vertical centering)
  - width: 220px per column
- .bracket-label: vertical text (rotated) for bracket name
- .grand-final-column: centered, larger column for the championship match
- .match-box: compact dark card, grid layout
  - .team-score-box: solid background square for scores
  - hover effects: border highlight, show edit/roll buttons
  - .map-pill: small chips for individual map scores (hidden until hover)
  - .round-grand_final: gold border + GRAND FINAL label above
- Connector lines (CSS pseudo-elements):
  - .match-box::after: horizontal line from right edge to next column
  - .match-box::before: vertical line between consecutive matches in same column
  - Color: semi-transparent gray
  - 22px offset matches column gap
- Mobile responsive: smaller columns on < 900px

Fixes:
- Tree layout now correctly separates upper/lower brackets with grand final as standalone column
- Matches are vertically centered in their column using flex space-around
- Compact match cards with clear score boxes
- Hidden edit/roll actions only appear on hover for less visual clutter
- Map details expand on hover to show extra info
- Bracket works for all 3 tournament types: Major (4 teams), Master (8 teams), Champion (8 teams)
